OL,3,CTravel warnings issued in Crete as
OL,4,Cdust storm turns skies bright red
OL,6,FIn Crete, an island off Greece's
OL,7,Fsouthern shore, extreme winds caused a
OL,8,FSaharan dust storm which turned the
OL,9,Fsky red and orange.
OL,11,FConcentrations of more than 1,000
OL,12,Fmicrograms of particles per cubic
OL,13,Fmetre of air were recorded in some
OL,14,Fparts of the island, according to the
OL,15,Fmeteorological office.
OL,17,FSahara dust storms are not uncommon in
OL,18,FCrete during the spring and summer
OL,19,Fmonths, but they are not typically
OL,20,Fthis severe.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
