OL,3,CTravel warnings issued in Crete as
OL,4,Cdust storm turns skies bright red
OL,6,FSaharan dust clouds are caused when
OL,7,Fpowerful winds lift fine particles of
OL,8,Fsand from the Sahara Desert up into
OL,9,Fthe atmosphere, which can then be
OL,10,Fcarried overseas.
OL,12,FSometimes the dust can mix with rain
OL,13,Fas it falls, becoming red droplets, in
OL,14,Fwhat is more commonly known as blood
OL,15,Frain.
OL,17,FNorth Africa also experienced extreme
OL,18,Fdust storms this week, with Libya's
OL,19,Fskies turning bright red and the city
OL,20,Fof Tobruk issuing a state of emergency
OL,21,Fon Wednesday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
